The most common answer to this question is:

\boxed{\text{reaction enthalpy (ΔH) and stoichiometry}}

This refers to determining the **enthalpy change (ΔH)** of the reaction and the **molar ratio (stoichiometry)** from isothermal titration calorimetry (ITC) data. The ITC curve directly provides heat flow, allowing calculation of ΔH per mole of reactant, while the stoichiometry is derived from the binding or reaction stoichiometry observed in the titration.
